dellNetIfExtensionMib.name: dellNetIfExtensionMib

revisions.description: Initial version of this mib module.

dellNetIfExtensionMib.description: Dell Networking OS IF Extenstion MIB.

dellNetIfTable.name: dellNetIfTable
dellNetIfTable.description: Dell Networking OS Extension ifTable contains generic interface parameters.

dellNetIfEntry.name: dellNetIfEntry
dellNetIfEntry.description: A row defintion of Dell Networking OS Interface Extension parameters.

dellNetIfIpMtu.name: dellNetIfIpMtu
dellNetIfIpMtu.description: The IP (Internet Protocol), Maximum Transmission Unit value.

dellNetIfDuplexMode.name: dellNetIfDuplexMode
dellNetIfDuplexMode.description: Duplex mode of the interface. This will be read-write only for s60

dellNetIfRxFlowCtrl.name: dellNetIfRxFlowCtrl
dellNetIfRxFlowCtrl.description: Flow control receive. This will be read-write only for s60

dellNetIfTxFlowCtrl.name: dellNetIfTxFlowCtrl
dellNetIfTxFlowCtrl.description: Flow Control transmit.This will be read-only only for s60

dellNetIfDescr.name: dellNetIfDescr
dellNetIfDescr.description: A textual string containing information about the interface. This will be read-write only for s60

dellNetIfAdminStatus.name: dellNetIfAdminStatus
dellNetIfAdminStatus.description: A admin status of any interface. This will be read-write only for s60

dellNetIfRateInterval.name: dellNetIfRateInterval
dellNetIfRateInterval.description: The rate info interval for the interface. This will be read-write only for s60

dellNetIfSpeed.name: dellNetIfSpeed
dellNetIfSpeed.description: The interface's current bandwidth in bits per second. This will be read-write only for s60

dellNetIfPortListBitPos.name: dellNetIfPortListBitPos
dellNetIfPortListBitPos.description: This is used for identifying the bit position in PortList Object for a given interface.

dellNetIfStaticsTable.name: dellNetIfStaticsTable
dellNetIfStaticsTable.description: The statistcs information of the interfaces for performance monitoring.

dellNetIfStaticsEntry.name: dellNetIfStaticsEntry
dellNetIfStaticsEntry.description: A row defintion of Dell Networking OS Extension interface statistics.

dellNetIfInVlanPkts.name: dellNetIfInVlanPkts
dellNetIfInVlanPkts.description: The total number of valid VLAN Tagged frames received.

dellNetIfIn64BytePkts.name: dellNetIfIn64BytePkts
dellNetIfIn64BytePkts.description: The total number of frames (including bad frames) received that were 64 octets in length (excluding framing bits but in-cluding FCS octets).

dellNetifIn65To127BytePkts.name: dellNetifIn65To127BytePkts
dellNetifIn65To127BytePkts.description: The total number of frames (including bad frames) received that were between 65 and 127 octets in length inclusive (ex-cluding framing bits but including FCS octets).

dellNetIfIn128To255BytePkts.name: dellNetIfIn128To255BytePkts
dellNetIfIn128To255BytePkts.description: The total number of frames (including bad frames) received that were between 128 and 255 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets).

dellNetIfIn256To511BytePkts.name: dellNetIfIn256To511BytePkts
dellNetIfIn256To511BytePkts.description: The total number of frames (including bad frames) received that were between 256 and 511 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets).

dellNetIfIn512To1023BytePkts.name: dellNetIfIn512To1023BytePkts
dellNetIfIn512To1023BytePkts.description: The total number of frames (including bad frames) received that were between 512 and 1023 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets).

dellNetIfInOver1023BytePkts.name: dellNetIfInOver1023BytePkts
dellNetIfInOver1023BytePkts.description: The total number of frames received that were longer than 1023 (1025 Bytes in case of VLAN Tag) octets (excluding framing bits, but including FCS octets) and were otherwise well formed. This counter is not incremented for too long frames.

dellNetIfInThrottles.name: dellNetIfInThrottles
dellNetIfInThrottles.description: This counter is incremented when a valid frame with a length or type field value equal to 0x8808 (Control Frame) is re-ceived.

dellNetIfInRunts.name: dellNetIfInRunts
dellNetIfInRunts.description: The total number of frames received that were less than 64 octets long (excluding framing bits, but including FCS octets) and were otherwise well formed.

dellNetIfInGiants.name: dellNetIfInGiants
dellNetIfInGiants.description: The total number of frames received that were longer than 1518 (1522 Bytes in case of VLAN Tag) octets (excluding framing bits, but including FCS octets) and were otherwise well formed. This counter is not incremented for too long frames.

dellNetIfInCRC.name: dellNetIfInCRC
dellNetIfInCRC.description: The total number of frames received that had a length (ex-cluding framing bits, but including FCS octets) of between 64 and 1518 octets, inclusive, but had a bad CRC.

dellNetIfInOverruns.name: dellNetIfInOverruns
dellNetIfInOverruns.description: The total number of frames dropped because of buffer issue.

dellNetIfOutVlanPkts.name: dellNetIfOutVlanPkts
dellNetIfOutVlanPkts.description: The Number of Good VLAN Tagged Frames sent successfully.

dellNetIfOutUnderruns.name: dellNetIfOutUnderruns
dellNetIfOutUnderruns.description: The total number of frames dropped because of buffer underrun.

dellNetIfOutUnicasts.name: dellNetIfOutUnicasts
dellNetIfOutUnicasts.description: The Number of Good Unicast Frames sent successfully.

dellNetIfOutCollisions.name: dellNetIfOutCollisions
dellNetIfOutCollisions.description: A count of the frames that due to excessive or late collisions are not transmitted successfully.

dellNetIfOutWredDrops.name: dellNetIfOutWredDrops
dellNetIfOutWredDrops.description: A count of the frames that are dropped using WRED policy because of to excessive traffic.

dellNetIfOut64BytePkts.name: dellNetIfOut64BytePkts
dellNetIfOut64BytePkts.description: The Number of Good Frames sent successfully whose size was 64 Bytes.

dellNetIfOut65To127BytePkts.name: dellNetIfOut65To127BytePkts
dellNetIfOut65To127BytePkts.description: The Number of Good Frames sent successfully whose size was in the range of 65 to 127 Bytes.

dellNetIfOut128To255BytePkts.name: dellNetIfOut128To255BytePkts
dellNetIfOut128To255BytePkts.description: The Number of Good Frames sent successfully whose size was in the range of 128 to 255 Bytes.

dellNetIfOut256To511BytePkts.name: dellNetIfOut256To511BytePkts
dellNetIfOut256To511BytePkts.description: The Number of Good Frames sent successfully whose size was in the range of 256 to 511 Bytes.

dellNetIfOut512To1023BytePkts.name: dellNetIfOut512To1023BytePkts
dellNetIfOut512To1023BytePkts.description: The Number of Good Frames sent successfully whose size was in the range of 512 to 1023 Bytes.

dellNetIfOutOver1023BytePkts.name: dellNetIfOutOver1023BytePkts
dellNetIfOutOver1023BytePkts.description: The Number of Good Frames sent successfully whose size was greater than 1023 Bytes.

dellNetIfOutThrottles.name: dellNetIfOutThrottles
dellNetIfOutThrottles.description: This counter is incremented when a valid frame with a length or type field value equal to 0x8808 (Control Frame) is sent.

dellNetIfLastDiscontinuityTime.name: dellNetIfLastDiscontinuityTime
dellNetIfLastDiscontinuityTime.description: The value of sysUpTime on the most recent occasion at which this interface's counters suffered a discontinuity via a reset. If no such discontinuities have occurred since the last reinitialization of the local management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

dellNetIfInCentRate.name: dellNetIfInCentRate
dellNetIfInCentRate.description: This is the ingress rate in percentage. This is an integer value which can go from 0 to 100.

dellNetIfOutCentRate.name: dellNetIfOutCentRate
dellNetIfOutCentRate.description: This is the egress rate in percentage. This is an integer value which can go from 0 to 100.

dellNetIfExtensionMibCompliance.name: dellNetIfExtensionMibCompliance
dellNetIfExtensionMibCompliance.description: The compliance statement for Dell Networking OS IF Extension MIB.

dellNetIfParamsGroup.name: dellNetIfParamsGroup
dellNetIfParamsGroup.description: A collection of objects providing the Dell Networking OS IF Extenstion parameters.

dellNetIfStatsGroup.name: dellNetIfStatsGroup
dellNetIfStatsGroup.description: A collection of objects providing the interface statistics.
